HEADWORD: Shin Shu
<hw>Shin Shu</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Jap., lit., true sect.]</ety>
<def>The leading and most progressive Buddhist sect of Japan, resting
its faith rather upon Amida than Gautama Buddha. Rites and ceremonies
are held useless without uprightness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

